<div class="vert">
  <h3 style="margin: 0;">Linked to a picker</h3>
  <forge-date-time-field id="demo-date-time-field" picker="demo-date-time-picker" name="appointment" label="Appointment" placeholder="Select date and time">
    <span slot="support-text">Pick when your appointment should start.</span>
  </forge-date-time-field>
  <forge-date-time-picker id="demo-date-time-picker" time-mode="single"></forge-date-time-picker>

  <forge-label-value>
    <span slot="label">Complete</span>
    <span slot="value" id="demo-complete">false</span>
  </forge-label-value>

  <forge-label-value>
    <span slot="label">Value</span>
    <pre slot="value" id="demo-value" style="margin: 0; font-family: monospace;">null</pre>
  </forge-label-value>

  <forge-button variant="raised" id="demo-validate">Report validity</forge-button>

  <hr style="width: 100%; border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--forge-theme-outline, #dadce0); margin: 8px 0;" />

  <h3 style="margin: 0;">Standalone — no picker</h3>
  <p style="margin: 0; max-width: 44ch; color: var(--forge-theme-text-medium, #5f6368);">
    With no <code>picker</code> attribute the field has no calendar toggle or popup — users type the date and time
    directly into the masked inputs.
  </p>
  <p style="margin: 0; max-width: 44ch; color: var(--forge-theme-text-medium, #5f6368);">
    Quick keys while a segment is focused: <kbd>n</kbd> = now, <kbd>t</kbd> = today. On blur / <kbd>Enter</kbd>
    loosely-typed entries are coerced like the picker: a two-digit year gains a century
    (<code>1/2/25</code> → <code>01/02/2025</code>), an hour-only time completes (<code>5</code> →
    <code>05:00&nbsp;AM</code>), and out-of-range parts clamp (<code>02/30/2025</code> → <code>02/28/2025</code>).
  </p>
  <forge-date-time-field id="demo-standalone-field" name="standalone" label="Standalone (no picker)" placeholder="Type a date and time">
    <span slot="support-text">No picker linked — type directly into the masked inputs.</span>
  </forge-date-time-field>

  <forge-label-value>
    <span slot="label">Complete</span>
    <span slot="value" id="demo-standalone-complete">false</span>
  </forge-label-value>

  <forge-label-value>
    <span slot="label">Value</span>
    <pre slot="value" id="demo-standalone-value" style="margin: 0; font-family: monospace;">null</pre>
  </forge-label-value>

  <hr style="width: 100%; border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--forge-theme-outline, #dadce0); margin: 8px 0;" />

  <h3 style="margin: 0;">Responsive wrapping — resize the containers</h3>
  <p style="margin: 0; max-width: 44ch; color: var(--forge-theme-text-medium, #5f6368);">
    A date + time range sits on one line when it fits and wraps by endpoint (start over end) when the
    container is too narrow. Each container below is resizable.
  </p>

  <div style="resize: horizontal; overflow: auto; padding: 12px; border: 1px dashed var(--forge-theme-outline, #dadce0); width: 640px; max-width: 100%;">
    <forge-date-time-field date-mode="range" time-mode="range" label="Event window" persist-mask>
      <span slot="support-text">Drag the container's corner to see it wrap.</span>
    </forge-date-time-field>
  </div>

  <div style="resize: horizontal; overflow: auto; padding: 12px; border: 1px dashed var(--forge-theme-outline, #dadce0); width: 260px; max-width: 100%;">
    <forge-date-time-field date-mode="range" time-mode="range" allow-seconds label="With seconds" persist-mask></forge-date-time-field>
  </div>

  <hr style="width: 100%; border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--forge-theme-outline, #dadce0); margin: 8px 0;" />

  <h3 style="margin: 0;">Label positions &amp; variants</h3>
  <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; max-width: 420px;">
    <forge-date-time-field label="Inset (default)" label-position="inset"></forge-date-time-field>
    <forge-date-time-field label="Block start" label-position="block-start"></forge-date-time-field>
    <forge-date-time-field label="Inline start" label-position="inline-start"></forge-date-time-field>
    <forge-date-time-field label="Tonal variant" variant="tonal"></forge-date-time-field>
    <forge-date-time-field label="Filled variant" variant="filled"></forge-date-time-field>
  </div>

  <hr style="width: 100%; border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--forge-theme-outline, #dadce0); margin: 8px 0;" />

  <h3 style="margin: 0;">Placeholder &amp; show-mask</h3>
  <p style="margin: 0; max-width: 46ch; color: var(--forge-theme-text-medium, #5f6368);">
    At rest the label / placeholder shows; the format guide appears on focus (<code>show-mask</code>
    on, the default) — <strong>click into each field</strong> to see it. An inset label rests inside
    the field. <code>persist-mask</code> pins the guide on even at rest. With <code>show-mask</code>
    off the guide never auto-shows.
  </p>
  <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; max-width: 420px;">
    <forge-date-time-field label="Inset label (rests, focus for guide)"></forge-date-time-field>
    <forge-date-time-field label="Placeholder (non-inset)" label-position="block-start" placeholder="Select date and time"></forge-date-time-field>
    <forge-date-time-field label="Persist mask (guide pinned)" label-position="block-start" persist-mask></forge-date-time-field>
    <forge-date-time-field id="demo-format-hints" label="show-mask off (hints only)" label-position="block-start"></forge-date-time-field>
  </div>
</div>

<script type="module" src="date-time-field.ts"></script>
